### 0.2 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Framework | **Next.js 14 (App Router)** | Server Components, Edge Runtime, built-in API routes |
| Language | **TypeScript 5 (strict)** | Type safety across the entire stack |
| Styling | **Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui** | Consistent, accessible component primitives |
| Auth | **Supabase Auth** | Email/password + magic link; RLS-enforced at DB level |
| Database | **Supabase (PostgreSQL)** | RLS policies; also used for rate limiting to avoid extra services |
| AI Provider | **Anthropic Claude** (primary) / GPT-4o (fallback) | Claude has better Swedish language quality |
| AI SDK | **Vercel AI SDK (`ai` package)** | Streaming, provider abstraction, React hooks |
| Payments | **Stripe** with Swish + card | Swish is critical for Swedish market adoption |
| Validation | **Zod** | Runtime type safety on all API boundaries |
| Error Tracking | **Sentry** | Capture errors without logging user content |
| Analytics | **Plausible Analytics** | Privacy-preserving, GDPR-compliant, cookieless |
| Deployment | **Vercel** | Zero-config Next.js deployment |

**Note on rate limiting:** We use Supabase (already in the stack) for per-user request tracking instead of adding Upstash Redis. This is sufficient for MVP scale and removes one external dependency. Add Redis only if abuse becomes a measurable problem.

**Note on AI model:** Before wiring up AI generation, verify the exact current model string in the [Anthropic API documentation](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/about-claude/models). Model string typos silently break generation. Use the latest Claude Sonnet model available.

